{
  "texts": [
    "Another avenue for exploration is meta-learning, where the model is trained to quickly adapt to new tasks or domains with limited labeled data.",
    "This could make the LM-LSTM-CRF framework more flexible and applicable in low-resource settings where labeled data are scarce.",
    "The proposed model demonstrated significant improvements in named entity recognition (NER) performance, particularly in handling overlapping mentions and complex entity structures.",
    "When evaluated on standard datasets containing overlapping entities, the model achieved notable increases in F1 scores, outperforming baseline methods traditionally used for this task.",
    "This enhanced performance is largely attributed to the model's ability to maintain linear time complexity, even as the complexity of mention structures increases."
  ]
}